description:
&lt;p&gt;Royal Cornwall Hospitals NHS Trust is the largest provider of healthcare in the county, and we are always keen to recruit enthusiastic and motivated people to join our hospitals as Healthcare Support Workers. We strive to deliver high quality, compassionate care for our patients and their families. A caring nature, good communication skills, and a willingness to learn and develop are essential for this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Healthcare Support Worker, you will work closely with our Registered Nurses and other healthcare staff to deliver fundamental care to patients, including assisting with personal hygiene, toileting needs, feeding and mobility. Previous experience within the speciality is desirable, but all successful applicants will receive a comprehensive induction on commencing the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for caring and compassionate people who either have experience of delivering care, or are interested in starting a career in a healthcare setting. We are looking for Healthcare Support Workers to work full time, on a rota basis covering Monday – Friday, weekends, nights and bank holidays. If you would like to be part of our team delivering brilliant care to our patients, we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All shortlisted applicants will be invited to interview via Microsoft Teams or Face-to-face at the Emergency Department, Royal Cornwall Hospital, Truro.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alice Dudley, ED Senior Sister or Polly Wells AP. Telephone 01872 25 3110 or email alice.dudley@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
